==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exoneration
<hw>Ex*on`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exoneratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>Exon⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of disburdening, discharging, or freeing morally from a
charge or imputation; also, the state of being disburdened or freed from
a charge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exonerative</ent>⟦br⟧
